Definition: marked by foolish or unreasoning fondness
Example: he was infatuated with her; Narcissus was a beautiful Greek youth who became enamored of his own reflection
Synonyms: noun, feeling, enamoredness, infatuated, in_love, potty, smitten, soft_on, p, taken_with, marked, by, foolish, or, unreasoning, fondness, he, was, with, her, Narcissus, a, beautiful, Greek, youth, who, became, of, his, own, reflection
Category: adj.all
